        <TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH=693 HEIGHT=133 COLSPAN=3>
                    
                      <div align="left">
                      <table border="0" width="696" height="136">
                        <tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-11-18 - Unable to find drivers for your Sound Card?</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> <div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">In order to help people find the newest drivers for their
sound cards, we have compiled a list of some of the places you can find them.
Thanks to all of you that helped us to create a list of cards at a starting
point, and especially to those of you that provided extra information. Thanks.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">Unfortunately, this list is by no means complete, but
hopefully it will be a good starting place.</font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><br>
<font color="#FF0000">
CREATIVE:</font>
&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">Go to this site and enter your operating system and card:<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66"><a href="http://www.soundblaster.com/drivers/">http://www.soundblaster.com/drivers/</a>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66"><br>
Sound Blaster cards:&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">Live! Family<br>
PCI512<br>
PCI128<br>
PCI64<br>
Ensonic AudioPCI<br>
AWE64 Series<br>
AWE32<br>
16<br>
Pro<br>
Sound Blaster<br>
Microchannel<br>
WaveBlaster/WaveBlaster II<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<br>
</font>
<font color="#FF0000">
GATEWAY:<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;If your Sound Blaster is integrated onto your Gateway
motherboard, Gateway has some new drivers for you. Use these instead of the
Creative drivers if you have an integrated Sound Blaster on your Gateway PC.&nbsp;Drivers for Creative Labs Audio PCI 64D and 128D Digital
Sound Card (1373 chipset) for part number 6000734, 6000955, 6001110, 6001238,
6001502 and Gateway motherboards with this integrated sound hardware.<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<a
href="http://www.gateway.com/support/product/drivers/sound/audiopci1373a.shtml">http://www.gateway.com/support/product/drivers/sound/audiopci1373a.shtml</a><o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;Drivers for Creative Labs Audio PCI 64V (1371 Chipset). <o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<a
href="http://www.gateway.com/support/product/drivers/sound/audiopci1371a.shtml">http://www.gateway.com/support/product/drivers/sound/audiopci1371a.shtml</a><o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">Please remember to make sure your motherboards part number
is on their list before installing the driver. *These are Gateway-specific
drivers for integrated Sound Blaster chips.* If you have got the retail
equivalent sound cards, or a non-Gateway system, its at your own risk.<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66"><br>
</font>
<font color="#FF0000">
TURTLE BEACH<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<a
href="http://www.voyetra-turtle-beach.com/site/sales_support/ftp.asp">http://www.voyetra-turtle-beach.com/site/sales_support/ftp.asp</a><o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">Cancun FX<br>
Daytona PCI<br>
Malibu Surround 64<br>
Maui<br>
Monte Carlo<br>
Montego A3DXstream<br>
Montego II<br>
Montego II Home Studio<br>
Montego II Plus<br>
Montego II VoiceXpress<br>
Montego II Quadzilla<br>
Monterey<br>
MultiSound Classic<br>
Quad Studio<br>
Santa Cruz<br>
WaveFront<br>
…and others.<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">DELL users: If your Turtle Beach sound card came with your
Dell computer, you will have to call Dell at the service number they provided
with your computer, or visit <a
href="http://support.dell.com/us/en/DHS-BSD_reg.asp?segid=5DS">http://support.dell.com/us/en/DHS-BSD_reg.asp?segid=5DS</a>
for help.<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66"><br>
</font>
<font color="#FF0000">
DIAMOND<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<a
href="http://www.diamondmm.com/default.asp?menu=support&amp;submenu=drivers">http://www.diamondmm.com/default.asp?menu=support&amp;submenu=drivers</a><o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;Scroll down until you see the Audio Products section. You
will be presented with three choices.<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">Monster Sound MX400<br>
Sonic Impact S100<br>
Legacy Devices<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">For the following cards, click on the Legacy Devices option:<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">Monster Sound MX300<br>
Monster Sound MX25<br>
Monster Sound MX200<br>
Monster Sound M80<br>
Monster Sound (Original)<br>
Sonic Impact S90<br>
Sonic Impact S70<br>
Sonic Sound LX<br>
Sonic Sound<br>
Sonic Vibes<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">Click on the device name that matches the card you have.
When the new page loads, look for the Drivers link at the top center of the
page (in the center box).<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66"><br>
</font>
<font color="#FF0000">
CRYSTAL AUDIO:</font>
<font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">These chips are made by a company called Cirrus Logic. They
do not actually make sound cards, just chips. Their web site can link you to
your manufacturer, or provide you with generic drivers.<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<a
href="http://www.cirrus.com/Drivers/audiodrv/index_new.cfm">http://www.cirrus.com/Drivers/audiodrv/index_new.cfm</a><o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">It is probably better to get your drivers from the card
manufacturer, if possible. To choose the proper generic drivers, you will need
to know your chipset, which should be in the manual that you were given with
your computer.<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">Crystal Audio CS4232 chip set burned into the
motherboard...a basic SB clone...<br>
Crystal SoundFusion(TM)<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal>&nbsp;</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FF0000">YAMAHA:<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<a href="http://www.yamahayst.com/lsi/dindex.htm">http://www.yamahayst.com/lsi/dindex.htm</a><o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;DS-1x&nbsp;<br>
YMF724<br>
YMF740<br>
YMF744<br>
YMF754<br>
OPL3-SAx<br>
YMF701<br>
YMF711<br>
YMF715<br>
YMF718<br>
YMF719<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">Note, these are also generic drivers, and you may want to
pursue drivers from your card manufacturer if possible.<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66"><br>
</font>
<font color="#FF0000">
ESS TECHNOLOGIES:</font>
<font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66"><a
href="http://www.esstech.com/Technical/drivers/downloadable/drivers/driver.htm">http://www.esstech.com/Technical/drivers/downloadable/drivers/driver.htm</a><o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FF0000">PCI Audio Devices</font>
<font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">ES1989<br>
ES19880<br>
ES1978<br>
ES1948<br>
ES1968<br>
ES1938-ES1946&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FF0000">ISA Audio Devices</font>
<font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">ES1888 <br>
ES1887 <br>
ES1879<br>
ES1878 <br>
ES1869 <br>
ES1868 <br>
ES1788 <br>
ES1688 <br>
ES688&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">You may have to search your computer documentation to find
the right ES# for your card or computer.<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<br>
</font>
<font color="#FF0000">
VOODOO:<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<a
href="http://www.3dfxgamers.com/drivers/latest_drivers.stm">http://www.3dfxgamers.com/drivers/latest_drivers.stm</a><o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">Voodoo 4/5<br>
Voodoo 3 3500 TV<br>
Voodoo 3<br>
Voodoo Banshee<br>
Voodoo 2<br>
Voodoo Rush<br>
Voodoo Graphics<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66"><br>
</font>
<font color="#FF0000">
ELSA:<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<a href="http://www3.elsa.de/www/filearea.nsf/files?openview">http://www3.elsa.de/www/filearea.nsf/files?openview</a><o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">ELSA AirLancer <br>
ELSA ECOMO <br>
ELSA ERAZOR <br>
ELSA GLADIAC <br>
ELSA GLoria <br>
ELSA LANCOM <br>
ELSA MicroLink <br>
ELSA MicroLink 56k <br>
ELSA MicroLink Cable <br>
ELSA MicroLink ISDN <br>
ELSA QuickStep <br>
ELSA REVELATOR <br>
ELSA Synergy <br>
ELSA TanGo <br>
ELSA VICTORY <br>
ELSA WINNER <br>
ELSAmovie <br>
ELSAvision <br>
Other products<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">To select the product, you need to click on the little
blue/green arrows to the left of the name (this had me confused for a bit).<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66"><br>
</font>
<font color="#FF0000">AUREAL:<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<a href="http://www.vortexofsound.com/drivers/drivers.htm">http://www.vortexofsound.com/drivers/drivers.htm</a><o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">Vortex SQ1500<br>
Vortex SQ2500<br>
Vortex SQ 3500 Turbo<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">This site also has drivers for a few other cards, such as:&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">Aztech PCI 338 A3D<br>
Terratec XLerate<br>
Videologic SonicVortex2<br>
Xitel Storm VX<br>
Xitel Storm Platinum<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<br>
<a href="http://www.drivershq.com/main_home.html">http://www.drivershq.com/main_home.html</a><o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<br>
</font>
<font color="#FF0000">
HEWLETTE PACKARD:<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">Go to this site and type in the name of your computer
(Pavillion, for example). Then find your PC on the list. It seems that a lot of
HP computers use an integrated sound and modem device, so you may need to look
under the heading for Modems.<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66"><a href="http://www.hp.com/cposupport/software.html">http://www.hp.com/cposupport/software.html</a><o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">
Keep in mind, install DirectX FIRST, then your audio and video drivers.<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font color="#FFFF66">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></font>
</p>

